erstanding of "normality" toward which such care aspires. At the core of Medicalizing Ethnicity is the very definition of multiculturalism used by a variety of institutional settings in an attempt to mandate equality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural pluralism. 0aEthnopsychologyzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aHispanic AmericansxMental health serviceszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aMedicalizationzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aPsychiatry, TransculturalzNew York (State)zNew York. 4aAnthropology. 4aLatin American & Caribbean Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171845840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501718458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501718458/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles